Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop the 
wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with salt and 
pepper, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. 
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop two thirds of the @garlic cloves{3}(unpeeled) into a small 
piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of oil and scrunch to enclose it. Peel and 
grate the remaining garlic (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @mixed herbs{1%sachet}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and 
@water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs, @panko breadcrumbs{10%grams} and the 
grated garlic, then add the @British beef mince{240%grams}. Season with pepper 
and mix together with your hands.

Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers and @British streaky bacon{4%rashers} onto a baking tray 
(use another tray if necessary) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven 
until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Cook 
> bacon thoroughly.

Once cooked, set the bacon aside on a #plate{} lined with kitchen paper.

At the same time, roast the garlic parcel in the oven until soft, 
~{10-12%minutes}.

While the burgers cook, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%grams}.

Once the garlic has roasted and cooled, cut the end with scissors, squeeze 
it out of the skin and mash with a #fork{}.

Pop the @coleslaw mix{120%grams}, roasted garlic and @mayonnaise{64%grams} into 
another large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then mix well to combine. 
Taste and season again if needed.

Once cooked, carefully place the cheese on top of the burgers and pop back 
into the oven until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

At the same time, add the @sliced burger buns{2} to the tray to warm through, 
~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, spread the @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} on the bun bases, 
then top with the cheesy burgers, crispy bacon and bun lids.

Serve with the wedges and slaw alongside.

Enjoy!